Sometimes getting him to spawn can be a pain, took me many kills of the placeholder to get him to spawn, but that's just bad luck I think.<br>
<br>
1) If you can grav flux a rogue up, you might be able to get sneak/hide to work.  But walking through the level in sneak mode the whole way is probably an infinite death loop.  You have to go past many many mobs to do this, as far as I know.  I think you also need a very high lockpicking skill, but I'm not 100% sure.<br>
<br>
2) I'm not sure about illusions, I didn't really get a chance to try them, when a necro is dressed up as a skeleton are undead aggressive to him?  The thing with that is, why not just charm it if you have a high level necro?<br>
<br>
3) There are living AND undead wanderers that move around up there.  I found a clearing when there were only undead in the tower, walked up to the human skeleton, but when I clicked the bottle on him, I became visible and got whacked bad.  A couple nights before I did this I had tested it on a skeleton in Nektulos, and I did NOT become visible.  Not sure what the problem is, but I deduced that I would require somebody to charm the skeleton.<br>
<br>
In the end, I had to have my level 50 enchanter buddy show up and charm the skeleton.  It worked extremely well since I had 4 other group members holding off the extra 2 mobs while I did the trade in.  If you do it right, you might even end up with ONLY the human skeleton (by breaking the spawn if there's a placeholder up there).<br>
